<section>
  <h2 class="heading-large" id="what-youll-do">What you’ll do</h2>

  <p>You can work as an economist for a wide range of government departments and agencies. You may also be able to work overseas, eg by joining the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s diplomatic service.</p>

  <p>You’ll be able to develop your expertise through postings in areas such as:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>macroeconomic modelling</li>
    <li>competition policy</li>
    <li>international financial issues</li>
    <li>labour market trends</li>
    <li>taxation</li>
    <li>housing benefits</li>
    <li>local government finance</li>
    <li>public health</li>
    <li>criminal justice</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Your responsibilities could include synthesizing evidence, producing briefing material, providing policy advice and conducting cost-benefit analyses.</p>
</section>

